<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-067-486  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 067 486.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 22 1990 v6 n3 p47(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New AboveX software eases PC-to-PC communications. (from AboveSoftware Inc.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smith, Gina.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Above Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   AboveX (Communications software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications softwareSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Gina SmithandM;Memory-management software maker Above Software Inc. last week announced itsfirst PC-to-PC communications package, which company officials said givesusers an easy-to-use platform for exchanging messages and files.andM;AboveX lets DOS and OS/2 users remotely exchange text and graphics files andschedule transfers in advance, without having to understand modem baud ratesand communications protocols, said Bob Rafferty, chairman of the Santa Ana,Calif., firm.andM;AboveX automatically initializes the modem, and can send and receive messagesin the background while users run a different application in the foreground,Rafferty said.andP;  Its character-based, icon-driven interface lets users easilystore, log and organize messages, and create reports on messages sent andreceived, he added.andM;&quot;PC-to-PC communications is the one area that has not caught up with othertechnology,&quot; Rafferty said.andP;  &quot;People are still communicating the way they didin the 1970s.&quot; AboveX's easy-to-use menus, prescheduling andcontext-sensitive help will bring that market more up to par, he said.andM;Other AboveX features include support for 10 user-definable security levelsand three levels of data encryption, including the federal government's DataEncryption System (DES).andM;AboveX will run on any IBM PC compatible or better, and requires at least DOS3.0 or OS/2 1.0 and a Hayes-compatible modem.andP;  Its suggested retail price is$495 for a two-unit pack.andM;Above Software can be contacted at (714) 545-1181.andO;</TEXT></DOC>